      • display

        void display(java.util.ArrayList<Task> tasks)
        Displays the provided list of Task objects.
        Parameters:

      • getTask

        Task getTask(int index)
      throws TaskNotFoundException
        Retrieves the Task object associated with the index provided. The general contract is that the display will associate an unique integer index to each Task object whenever display(ArrayList) is called
        Parameters:
        index - Integer index associated with a displayed Task object
        Returns:
        Task object associated with the provided index
        Throws:
        TaskNotFoundException - Thrown when the provided index is out of bounds

      • feedback

        void feedback(FeedbackMessage f)
        Displays the provided FeedbackMessage object to the user. The FeedbackMessage object encapsulates the feedback message text as well as the styling with which to display the message
        Parameters:
        f - FeedbackMessage object to be displayed
        See Also:
        FeedbackMessage

      • getFeedbackMessageString

        java.lang.String getFeedbackMessageString()
        Retrieves the string message content of the last FeedbackMessage object that was displayed.
        Returns:
        String message content of last displayed FeedbackMessage object.

      • pushFilter

        void pushFilter(Filter filter)
        Adds the provided Filter object to the filter chain. The filtered list of Task objects will then be displayed
        Parameters:
        filter - Filter object to add to the filter chain

      • popFilter

        Filter popFilter()
        Removes the final Filter object in the filter chain and returns it. If only the root filter is remaining, this method does nothing and returns null
        Returns:
        Popped Filter object or null if only the root Filter remains

      • showChangeDataFilePathDialog

        boolean showChangeDataFilePathDialog()
        Shows a file picker dialog which prompts the user to select a FunDUE data file. Returns true if a file is successfully chosen, the user's preference will be updated and the selected file will used as the FunDUE data file.
        Returns:
        True if a file was selected, false otherwise.

      • showHelpPage

        boolean showHelpPage()
        Shows the window containing the FunDUE Help Page. Return value indicates whether the window was opened by the method.
        Returns:
        True if the FunDUE Help Page was shown, false if the window was already showing.

      • focusCommandBar

        Retrieves the UI elements to be displayed in a Parent container.
        Returns:
        Parent object to be displayed.
